bug.short_desc: IE9 shows ellipsis when not needed

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 789 Screenshot
Tested Feed Reader with IE9 Preview (1.9.7916.6000)
Have a look at the attached screenshot.

IE9 (1.9.7916.6000) Preview 4 has a problem here, have a look at the attached test case. Both labels has the width of 46px, but the first label shows ellipsis.
Reported the bug to Microsoft: https://connect.microsoft.com/IE/feedback/details/593849/ie9-shows-ellipsis-when-not-needed

Applied a workaround on trunk with r23224.
I keep the bug open as reminder.
Tested with IE9 Beta (9.0.7930.16406) and the issue still exists. I keep the bug open as reminder to test it with the next IE9 release.
Issue still exists with IE9 Preview 6 (1.9.8006.6000)

Set the workaround as final, because Microsoft closed the bug (see link in comment #2) as "won't fix".
Done on trunk with r23883.
Created a reminder bug #4346 to check if the browser bug is fixed with the next release.
